Rihanna, who was officially certified a billionaire in August 2021, made her debut on the list as a result of her beauty and lingerie empire, landing at the 1,729 spots on the annual list, Kanye, now officially Ye, is at spot 1,513, while Rapper Jay-Z is 2,076 on the billionaireâ€™s list.
According to Forbes, Rihanna, who is expecting her first child with ASAP Rocky, is reportedly the first billionaire to come from Barbados.
Forbes also announced that the world now has 2,668 billionaires with a collective net worth of $12.7 trillion.
Other celebrities who made the list include Kim Kardashian, who is listed at number 1,645, Tyler Perry, number 2,578 and Oprah Winfrey at 1,196
